## Design Considerations

### Test Design Principles
- **Deterministic:** No network calls, mock all external dependencies
- **Isolated:** Each test resets IndexedDB state (`beforeEach`)
- **Fast:** Parallelize where possible, optimize for <5min total runtime
- **Maintainable:** DRY test fixtures, clear test names, semantic assertions

### Test Data Strategy
- **Factory pattern:** `createMockTask({ title, priority, dueDate })` for readable test setup
- **Realistic data:** Use production-like data shapes (avoid trivial "test" strings)
- **Edge cases:** Empty strings, null dates, max-length strings, unicode characters

### CI/CD Integration
- **Run on:** Every commit, every PR, before merge to main
- **Fail fast:** Abort on first failure in CI, run all locally for debugging
- **Reporting:** HTML report for local debugging, JSON for CI dashboards
- **Retry:** Flaky test auto-retry (max 2 retries) to reduce false negatives

### Performance
- **Target:** All E2E tests complete in <5 minutes
- **Optimization:** Run tests in parallel (Playwright workers), minimize page reloads
- **Monitoring:** Track test duration over time, flag regressions

