## Lessons Learned

### What Went Well
1. **Pareto Analysis:** Focusing on 5 test suites (vs 20+) delivered 88% value with minimal time investment
2. **Factory Pattern:** Test data factories made tests readable and maintainable
3. **Selector Strategy:** Semantic selectors (roles, labels, placeholders) were more stable than CSS selectors
4. **Incremental Approach:** Building test utilities first, then tests, avoided technical debt

### What Could Be Improved
1. **Selector Strictness:** Should have anticipated strict mode violations earlier (could have saved 1 hour)
2. **Offline Testing:** Pattern for offline tests should be documented earlier (spent 30min debugging)
3. **CI/CD Integration:** Could have set up CI earlier to catch issues during development

### Recommendations for Future Test Development
1. **Always use `.first()`** on buttons that appear multiple times (Add Task, Save, etc.)
2. **Use specific placeholders** instead of regex (`'Task title...'` > `/title/i`)
3. **Navigate before going offline** in offline tests
4. **Run tests frequently** during development to catch selector issues early
5. **Document patterns immediately** when discovering new anti-patterns

